messages.message: hello backend engineers, quick PSA that @daniel made a function write_ibdoc (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/e18433bb13adcde36e1d964b752b0f6041591c10/shared-utils/py-utils/reader-utils/src/py/instabase/reader_utils/ibdoc_utils.py#L384) to write ibdocs to a path, and the functions handles writing it as either an ibdoc v1 or v2 + either as ibdoc or ibmsg!
